HEADWORD: Bromal
<hw>Bro"mal</hw> <pr>(br⟦omac⟧"m⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Brom</ets>ine + <ets>al</ets>dehyde.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An oily, colorless fluid,
<chform>CBr3.COH</chform>, related to bromoform, as chloral is to
chloroform, and obtained by the action of bromine on alcohol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

